                                        <p class="sub-heading margin-top-33 line-height-24">According to the World Bank Kampala May 2023 report, about 30% of Ugandans are poor. In absolute term, the number of poor people increased from 8.03 million to 8.31 million, which needs more attention and more interventions from government and private sector.</p>
